%20with%20me%20to%20each%20new%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20the%20first%20one%20to%20arrive%20and%20the%20last%20one%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20been%20the%20person%20who%20starts%20work%20early.%20As%20a%20mom%2C%20it's%20just%20worked%20out%20better%20for%20my%20schedule.%20But%20there%20is%20such%20a%20thing%20as%20being%20too%20early%20to%20work%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20work%20remotely%20and%20have%20a%20habit%20of%20checking%20chat%20channels%20before%20you've%20even%20had%20a%20coffee%20or%20a%20shower.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhile%20working%20with%20Dave%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20take%20time%20for%20myself%20early%20in%20the%20morning%20before%20the%20day's%20chaos%20got%20underway.%20Instead%20of%20spending%20an%20hour%20chit-chatting%20on%20group%20channels%2C%20I'll%20now%20take%20an%20extra%20hour%20to%20read%2C%20work%20out%2C%20and%20do%20my%20own%20thing%20before%20I%20start%20the%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20on%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20I've%20learned%20to%20set%20myself%20%26quot%3Baway%26quot%3B%20and%20truly%20unplug%20in%20the%20evening.%20I%20had%20to%20remove%20Slack%20from%20my%20phone%20to%20make%20myself%20do%20this%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You%20don't%20always%20need%20to%20clock%20an%20exact%20eight-hour%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20find%20remote%20work%20has%20made%20us%20harder%20on%20ourselves.%20We%20often%20go%20out%20of%20our%20way%20to%20prove%20that%20we're%20working%20or%20to%20make%20up%20for%20even%20a%20minute%20of%20lost%20time.%20Yet%2C%20a%20regular%20workday%20has%20its%20fair%20share%20of%20interruptions%20and%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20I%20work%20plenty%20of%2010%20or%2011-hour%20days%20just%20because%20of%20projects%20or%20deadlines%2C%20but%20I%20flex%20it%20out.%20If%20I%20have%20a%20kid's%20basketball%20game%20to%20go%20to%20or%20an%20appointment%20to%20make%2C%20it's%20totally%20fine%20if%20I%20clock%20in%20about%20seven%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20It's%20important%20to%20make%20time%20for%20your%20own%20personal%20hobbies%20and%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20working%20with%20Dave%2C%20I%20noticed%20he%20always%20did%20stuff%20on%20evenings%20and%20weekends%20%E2%80%94%20fishing%2C%20gardening%2C%20winemaking%2C%20and%20so%20much%20more.%20Plus%2C%20he%20actually%20left%20work%20on%20time%20so%20he%20could%20enjoy%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDave%20clearly%20had%20another%20life%20outside%20of%20work%2C%20and%20it%20made%20me%20remember%20some%20hobbies%20of%20my%20own.%20Soon%2C%20I%20stopped%20sneaking%20in%20extra%20work%20at%20night%20and%20got%20back%20into%20my%20own%20hobbies%20like%20reading%20and%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20When%20you're%20on%20vacation%2C%20you%20should%20truly%20be%20on%20vacation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20so%20many%20of%20us%20working%20remotely%20now%2C%20it's%20really%20easy%20to%20do%20a%20quick%20check-in%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20you%20are.%20Many%20of%20us%20have%20apps%20on%20our%20phones%2C%20and%20it%20just%20becomes%20a%20habit%20to%20be%20plugged%20into%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20answering%20some%20messages%20while%20on%20vacation%2C%20and%20Dave%20immediately%20told%20me%20to%20unplug.%20I%20had%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20prep%20before%20I%20left%2C%20and%20he%20assured%20me%20there%20was%20nothing%20that%20couldn't%20wait%20until%20I%20returned.%20He%20said%20he%20knew%20how%20to%20reach%20me%20if%20absolutely%20necessary%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20me%20step%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20I've%20really%20made%20myself%20unplug%20on%20vacation.%20For%20example%2C%20I've%20removed%C2%A0%20Slack%20on%20my%20phone%2C%20and%20setting%20that%20boundary%20has%20helped%20tremendously.%20Plus%2C%20I've%20never%20had%20anyone%20at%20work%20question%20why%20I'm%20not%20online.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20It's%20OK%20to%20take%20time%20for%20yourself%20during%20the%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20be%20so%20worried%20about%20proving%20myself%20that%20I%20rarely%20took%20time%20to%20go%20out%20to%20lunch%20with%20a%20friend%20or%20head%20out%20for%20a%20walk%20to%20clear%20my%20mind.%20Dave%20encouraged%20me%20to%20go%20outside%20to%20brainstorm%20or%20go%20to%20the%20occasional%20midday%20yoga%20because%20it%20was%20when%20I%20could%20fit%20it%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStepping%20away%20from%20work%20like%20this%20has%20never%20impacted%20my%20ability%20to%20do%20my%20job.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20believe%20it%20helped%20me%20do%20my%20job%20better.%20Now%2C%20I%20use%20this%20responsibly%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20an%20everyday%20thing%20where%20I'm%20out%20for%20hours.%20However%2C%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20best%20things%20I've%20learned%20to%20do%20for%20myself%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20remote%20worker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20a%20good%20work-life%20balance%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20was%20my%20worst%20enemy.%20I%20was%20the%20one%20who%20was%20overextending%20myself%20and%20finding%20reasons%20to%20put%20in%20extra%20hours%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20get%20wrapped%20up%20in%20the%20daily%20hustle%20and%20lose%20sight%20of%20what's%20important.%20Honestly%2C%20I%20still%20lose%20sight%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20but%20I'm%20far%20better%20and%20happier%20with%20my%20work-life%20balance%20than%20I've%20ever%20been%2C%20thanks%20to%20Dave%20and%20his%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EStacy%20Tornio%20is%20a%20journalist%2C%20marketer%2C%20and%20content%20director.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-work-life-balance-advice-boss-lessons-job-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704708121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659b96001c5c7b8c9a0eaffc%3