C%22Accessing%20your%20Apple%20Pay%20account%20in%20Apple%20Wallet%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6597e4446979d7371820add7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221158%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESelect%20the%20card%20you%20want%20to%20see%20and%20you'll%20get%20a%20list%20of%20your%20recent%20transactions.%3Cp%3EDave%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EIs%20Apple%20Pay%20Later%20a%20credit%20card%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fapple-pay-later-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20Pay%20Later%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20technically%20a%20one-time%20loan%2C%20not%20a%20credit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20Apple%20Pay%20Later%20is%20a%20buy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20(BNPL)%20financial%20service%20that%20works%20with%20your%20existing%20debit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20Pay%20Later%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20the%20cost%20of%20an%20item%20over%20a%20series%20of%20payments.%20You%20make%20the%20first%20payment%20when%20you%20purchase%20the%20item%20using%20any%20debit%20card%20already%20loaded%20in%20your%20Apple%20Wallet.%20Then%2C%20you%20make%20three%20additional%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20one%20every%20two%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%20over%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20the%20difference%20between%20Apple%20Pay%20and%20Apple%20Pay%20Later%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20Pay%20is%20a%20mobile%20payment%20system%20that%20leverages%20your%20existing%20credit%20or%20debit%20cards%20to%20make%20contactless%20payments%20in%20retail%20stores.%20Apple%20Pay%20also%20works%20in%20apps%20and%20online%20at%20select%20stores.%20Apple%20Pay%20Later%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20a%20loan%20option%20you%20can%20choose%20while%20making%20a%20payment%20within%20Apple%20Pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Apple%20Pay%2C%20Apple%20Pay%20Later%20only%20works%20with%20a%20debit%20card%20and%20is%20only%20available%20when