3E%20India%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20missed%20its%20fuel%20efficiency%20target%20for%20passengers%20vehicles%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202023%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20initiative%2C%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20that%20India%20has%20failed%20to%20achieve%20this%20target%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Fauto-news%2Fpassenger-vehicle-makers-miss-fuel-efficiency-targets%2Farticleshow%2F106617808.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quoting%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20makers%20of%C2%A0passengers%20vehicles%20comprising%20cars%2C%20vans%2C%20and%20utility%20vehicles%20achieved%20corporate%20average%20fuel%20economy%20(CAF%C3%89)%20%E2%80%93%20a%20measure%20of%20carbon%20emission%20of%20a%20vehicle%20%E2%80%93%20of%20116.078%20gm%20per%20km%20in%20the%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20paper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20such%20vehicles%20have%20crossed%20the%20CO2%20threshold%20of%20113%20gm%20per%20km%20set%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20%26amp%3B%20Highways.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fauto%2Findian-carmakers-may-have-to-pay-up-to-370-crore-for-violating-emissions-norms-18296411.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNBC%20TV18%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20reported%20that%20the%20target%20applies%20for%20the%20industry-average%20kerb%20weight%20of%201145%20kg%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%20reports%20had%20said%20that%20carmakers%20could%20face%20penalties%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%20370%20crore%20for%20violating%20emission%20rules%20according%20to%20the%20upgraded%20Corporate%20Average%20Fuel%20Efficiency%20II%20or%20CAFE%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Energy%20Conservation%20law%20mandates%20carmakers%20to%20pay%20Rs%2025%2C000%20per%20unit%20if%20their%20fleet%20C